Part I: Maps

Map Production: Michigan Aurora Borealis Photography Sites

This map displays potential photography sites as point data by a suitability ranking attribute that was created using a Multi Criteria Decision Analysis (MCDA). The suitability ranking is a comparing sites on their suitability as potential Aurora Borealis Photography locations. As the Aurora can often be seen by a cameras sensor when it remains undetectable to the human eye, predetermined suitable sites are necessary for Aurora photographers.

The Map

Link To WebMap

This WebMap is available here:

https://umass-amherst.maps.arcgis.com/apps/StoryMapBasic/index.html?appid=a04b9d1082514a709011f703811b7271

Input Data and Methodology

Aurora photography suitability data from previous MCDA suitability analysis.

More information is available here: https://umass-amherst.maps.arcgis.com/home/item.html?id=2daa35832a394125937132185e2f5797

These data points were selected and ranked using several suitability factors, based upon original input point data from The State of Michigans GIS Open Data Database (https://gis-michigan.opendata.arcgis.com/)

Map Production: Morchella Americana Distribution in North America

The purpose of this map production was to demonstrate the capabilities of ArcGIS Online in displaying spatial data in interesting and illuminating ways. Edited and symbolized point data is shown in comparison to raw imported point data downloaded from GBIF (https://www.gbif.org/)

Edited Input Map

The intention of these to maps was to show how data can be improved upon. Here is an example of data edited and symbolized in a meaningful way.
